cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image enhancement and object detection, which are primarily computer vision (cs.CV) problems. The use of vector embeddings and machine learning techniques to detect and remove occlusions also suggests a strong presence of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves inpainting, which is a graphics (cs.GR) problem. Finally, the use of datasets and user studies suggests a multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
